---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import { devlogPosts } from "../data/content";
---

<Base title="Project Cognify">
  <header>
    <h1 class="hero-title">Project Cognify</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">
      Investigating adolescent attention in an age of engineered distraction
    </p>
  </header>

  <div class="prose intro">
    <p>
      Project Cognify is a student-led research project built around a question we kept running into ourselves: Why is it so easy to spend hours focused on a game, yet so difficult to stay focused on schoolwork? We're Jonathan, Jeremy, and Ryan, three high school students investigating that question independently. Instead of starting with a solution, we started with research. We reviewed academic literature, surveyed students, conducted interviews, and let the evidence shape where the project would go. What we found challenged some of our original assumptions. We began by focusing on FOMO, but the research pointed toward something broader: motivation, social presence, and accountability may play a bigger role in helping students stay engaged than we expected. Our first prototype, [Cohort](/cohort), tests one of those ideas: whether simply knowing your friends are studying alongside you can make it easier to stay focused. We're building it now, and we're  curious as to whether it will work.
    </p>
  </div>

  <section class="recent">
    <p class="label">Recent devlog entries</p>
    <div class="entries">
      {
        devlogPosts.slice(0, 4).map((post) => (
          <article class="entry">
            <p class="meta">
              <time datetime={post.dateISO}>{post.date}</time>
              {post.author && (
                <>
                  <span>—</span>
                  <span>{post.author}</span>
                </>
              )}
            </p>
            <h3>
              <a href={`/devlog#${post.id}`}>{post.title}</a>
            </h3>
            <p class="entry__excerpt">{post.excerpt}</p>
            <a class="link-sm" href={`/devlog#${post.id}`}>
              read more →
            </a>
          </article>
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .intro {
    margin: 3.5rem 0;
  }

  .intro p {
    font-size: 1.06rem;
  }

  .recent {
    margin-top: 3.5rem;
  }

  .recent .entries {
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }
</style>
